# Cloudflare Pages — response headers.
#
# Strategy: hashed asset chunks are content-addressed (Vite stamps a
# build-hash into every filename under /assets/), so they're safe to
# cache for a year. EVERYTHING ELSE — including the root `/` and any
# SPA route like `/app/profile` that serves index.html via the
# `/*  /index.html  200` rewrite in _redirects — must be revalidated
# every visit, otherwise users keep loading a stale index.html that
# references chunk filenames a fresh deploy has already replaced
# (which 404s back to index.html with text/html and tanks every
# dynamic import).

/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Permissions-Policy: camera=(), microphone=(), geolocation=()

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
